Two children died  when a large rock was thrown at their moving vehicle from an overhead bridge in December 2017. CAPE TOWN - Three people have been arrested in connection with a deadly stone-throwing incident in Tongaat. Two children died when a large rock was thrown at their moving vehicle from an overhead bridge in December 2017. Police have only now made a breakthrough in their investigation. The two suspects face murder and attempted murder charges. The children's father was also seriously injured in the ensuing accident. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)